headline: Stocks dip slightly as investors return from Christmas holiday in light trading
summary: Stocks edged lower in light trading on Wall Street as investors returned from the Christmas holiday.  The S&P 500 index slipped less than 0.1% Friday, the Dow Jones Industrial Average also fell less than 0.1%, and the Nasdaq composite fell 0.1%.  Institutional investors have largely closed out their positions for the year.
